<span id="freeTextContainer5751907614058232806">This is my first Daniel Silva book, if fans of Silva can imagine, but can guarantee it won&apos;t be my last. I was looking for something to wake me up from the doldrums of Atwood, and this fit the bill nicely. <br/><br/>No sense wasting too much pen and ink on this review: if you&apos;re a fan of thrillers/spy novels, then this will satisfy every itch. Just like the jacket promises, it is indeed &quot;heart-stopping, seductive ... you won&apos;t be able to put it down.&quot; <br/><br/>It is indeed, and I couldn&apos;t. </span>
  <span id="freeText5751907614058232806" style="display:none">This is my first Daniel Silva book, if fans of Silva can imagine, but can guarantee it won't be my last. I was looking for something to wake me up from the doldrums of Atwood, and this fit the bill nicely. <br /><br />No sense wasting too much pen and ink on this review: if you're a fan of thrillers/spy novels, then this will satisfy every itch. Just like the jacket promises, it is indeed "heart-stopping, seductive ... you won't be able to put it down." <br /><br />It is indeed, and I couldn't. </span>
