<div id="review_3293067650" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3293067650" />
    <a title="Mark" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6755739-mark"><img alt="Mark" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1382617992p2/6755739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3293067650?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mark" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mark" href="/user/show/6755739-mark">Mark</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780008104733" href="/book/show/34120187-house-of-spies">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6755739-mark?shelf=american-writers">american-writers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6755739-mark?shelf=spies">spies</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6755739-mark?shelf=daniel-silva">daniel-silva</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6755739-mark?shelf=gabriel-allon">gabriel-allon</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6755739-mark?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3293067650" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3768019764094355656">This book about the activities of Gabriel Allon, by now director of the office (boss of the Israeli secret service or MOSSAD), in his last book he got trumped by Saladin who wrecked parts of the American security services and after his escape from America continued his activities in Europe.<br/><br/>Once again the French, British and Israeli security services devise a plot to get to Saladin. In the proces they will get to take on the drugs empire in North Africa and France. In doing so they will also take</span>
  <span id="freeText3768019764094355656" style="display:none">This book about the activities of Gabriel Allon, by now director of the office (boss of the Israeli secret service or MOSSAD), in his last book he got trumped by Saladin who wrecked parts of the American security services and after his escape from America continued his activities in Europe.<br /><br />Once again the French, British and Israeli security services devise a plot to get to Saladin. In the proces they will get to take on the drugs empire in North Africa and France. In doing so they will also take out a famous character from French Elite society, as they do not have to act like policemen they get to entrap this person and use him to lure Saladin from his hideout. Once again it takes the specialists from MI5 &amp; MI6, the French special service and Gabriel Allon with his team of special operatives to bring everything to a satisfactory ending. Even if their allies from the United States do their best to take control of the activities it is the manpower on the ground that makes the difference. From the South of France to London &amp; Paris to Morocco and the Sahara Desert and back the adventures does tick every box.<br /><br />Another satisfactory Gabriel Allon outing that is seriously larger in scale and in essence ends the Saladin tale, it also tells about drugs smuggling in the Mediterranean and gives a bit more insight in the war in the Middle East as Silva tends to waive into his books. Makes me wonder how he'll react on the peace-plan of Trumps son-in-law in a future book. The response to the new inhabitant in the White House is well hidden except for the politics of the professional spy services in the US which shows a clear dislike. <br /><br />Well worth your reading time if you first read the previous book "Black widow"by Silva. perhaps it is the wish of the publisher to recant the activities from this previous book in order to obtain first time readers. And yes it took the pace a wee bit out of the story at times. <br />The Silva books do not fail to live up to their reputation and this one is no exception. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3768019764094355656" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

